[121.489419, "o", "# Pipeline Checkpoint Resume - Bug Fixes\r\n\r\n## Problems Identified\r\n\r\nThe checkpoint/resume functionality had three critical bugs:\r\n\r\n### 1. **Semantic Mismatch Bug (CRITICAL)**\r\n- **Problem**: `save_checkpoint(batch_num)` saved the batch number (e.g., 5 for 5000 records) but stored it as 'last_line'\r\n- **Impact**: On resume, the code compared line number `i < start_from`, so if batch_num=5, it only skipped 5 lines instead of 5000\r\n- **Fix**: Changed to save `records_processed` (actual line/record number) instead of batch number\r\n\r\n### 2. **Buffer Flush Bug**\r\n- **Problem**: Checkpoint file opened with `open('.checkpoint', 'w')` without context manager or flush\r\n- **Impact**: Data might not be written to disk before a crash, leaving stale or empty checkpoint"]
[121.48947, "o", "\r\n- **Fix**: Use context manager with explicit `f.flush()` and `os.fsync()` to ensure data reaches disk\r\n\r\n### 3. **Data Overwrite Bug**\r\n- **Problem**: Used `INSERT OR REPLACE` which overwrites existing aggregates instead of accumulating\r\n- **Impact**: On resume, previously aggregated data was replaced instead of added to, causing data loss\r\n- **Fix**: Changed to `UPDATE` with addition (accumulation), falling back to `INSERT` for new categories\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- Tested by processing 50,000 records\r\n- Killed process at 25,000 records\r\n- Resumed from checkpoint\r\n- Verified final results match a full uninterrupted run (identical output)\r\n\r\n## Result\r\n\r\nCheckpoint/resume now works correctly:\r\n- Kills midway preserve progress\r\n- Restarts resume from exact position\r\n- No data duplication or loss\r\n- Proper accumulation of aggregates\r\n"]
[121.48962, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[121.489648, "o", "root@3b83cadd2721:/home/user/pipeline# "]
